  "texts": [
    "Weighted averaging assigns different weights to the predictions of individual models before combining them, while stacking involves training a meta-learner that learns how to combine the predictions of the base models.The weights for each model have been defined to determine the importance of their prediction in the final ensemble, ensuring their sum is equal to 1.",
    "The weights are assigned as follows: DT (0.1), RF (0.2), SVM (0.2), k-NN (0.2), and ANN (0.3).",
    "With the defined weights, the chosen ensemble method has been applied to combine the predictions of individual models.",
    "For weighted averaging, a weighted average of the predictions has been calculated.",
    "For stacking, a meta-learner has been trained on top of the predictions from individual models."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}